{
  "$defs": {
    "DilutionSecurity": {
      "description": "A dilutive security for the treasury stock method.\n\nUsed to compute diluted shares outstanding from options, warrants,\nRSUs, or convertible instruments.",
      "properties": {
        "exercise_price": {
          "description": "Exercise or strike price per share (0.0 for RSUs/convertibles with no cost).",
          "format": "double",
          "type": "number"
        },
        "name": {
          "description": "Descriptive name (e.g., \"Employee Stock Options\").",
          "type": "string"
        },
        "quantity": {
          "description": "Number of shares issuable upon exercise/conversion.",
          "format": "double",
          "type": "number"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "name",
        "quantity",
        "exercise_price"
      ],
      "type": "object"
    },
    "EquityBridge": {
      "description": "Structured equity bridge for converting Enterprise Value to Equity Value.\n\nStandard professional bridge:\n```text\nEquity = EV - Total Debt + Cash - Preferred Equity - Minority Interest\n         + Non-Operating Assets + Σ(other adjustments)\n```\n\nWhen attached to a [`DiscountedCashFlow`], this takes precedence over the\nflat `net_debt` scalar.",
      "properties": {
        "cash": {
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Cash and cash equivalents.",
          "format": "double",
          "type": "number"
        },
        "minority_interest": {
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Non-controlling (minority) interests.",
          "format": "double",
          "type": "number"
        },
        "non_operating_assets": {
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Non-operating assets (excess cash, investments, real estate, etc.).",
          "format": "double",
          "type": "number"
        },
        "other_adjustments": {
          "description": "Named adjustments (e.g., unfunded pension, contingent liabilities).\nPositive values increase equity; negative values decrease it.",
          "items": {
            "maxItems": 2,
            "minItems": 2,
            "prefixItems": [
              {
                "type": "string"
              },
              {
                "format": "double",
                "type": "number"
              }
            ],
            "type": "array"
          },
          "type": "array"
        },
        "preferred_equity": {
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Preferred stock at liquidation preference.",
          "format": "double",
          "type": "number"
        },
        "total_debt": {
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Total interest-bearing debt.",
          "format": "double",
          "type": "number"
        }
      },
      "type": "object"
    },
    "TerminalValueSpec": {
      "description": "Terminal value calculation method for DCF.",
      "oneOf": [
        {
          "description": "Gordon Growth Model: TV = FCF_terminal × (1 + g) / (WACC - g)",
          "properties": {
            "growth_rate": {
              "description": "Perpetual growth rate (e.g., 0.02 for 2%)",
              "format": "double",
              "type": "number"
            },
            "type": {
              "const": "gordon_growth",
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "type",
            "growth_rate"
          ],
          "type": "object"
        },
        {
          "description": "Exit Multiple: TV = Terminal_Metric × Multiple",
          "properties": {
            "multiple": {
              "description": "Multiple to apply (e.g., 10.0 for 10x EBITDA)",
              "format": "double",
              "type": "number"
            },
            "terminal_metric": {
              "description": "Terminal metric value (e.g., EBITDA)",
              "format": "double",
              "type": "number"
            },
            "type": {
              "const": "exit_multiple",
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "type",
            "terminal_metric",
            "multiple"
          ],
          "type": "object"
        },
        {
          "description": "H-Model: linear fade from high growth to stable growth (Damodaran).\n\n```text\nTV = FCF_T × (1+g_s)/(WACC-g_s) + FCF_T × H × (g_h-g_s)/(WACC-g_s)\n```\n\nwhere `H` is the half-life in years of the high-growth fade period.\nThe first term is the standard Gordon Growth stable-state value;\nthe second term captures the present value of excess growth that\nlinearly decays from `high_growth_rate` to `stable_growth_rate`\nover `2 × half_life_years`.",
          "properties": {
            "half_life_years": {
              "description": "Half-life of the growth fade in years (e.g., 5.0).",
              "format": "double",
              "type": "number"
            },
            "high_growth_rate": {
              "description": "Initial high growth rate (e.g., 0.15 for 15%).",
              "format": "double",
              "type": "number"
            },
            "stable_growth_rate": {
              "description": "Long-run stable growth rate (e.g., 0.03 for 3%). Must be < WACC.",
              "format": "double",
              "type": "number"
            },
            "type": {
              "const": "h_model",
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "type",
            "high_growth_rate",
            "stable_growth_rate",
            "half_life_years"
          ],
          "type": "object"
        }
      ]
    },
    "ValuationDiscounts": {
      "description": "Valuation discounts for private company equity.\n\nApplied multiplicatively after the equity bridge:\n```text\nFMV = Equity Value × (1 - DLOC) × (1 - DLOM) × (1 - other_discount)\n```\n\nThe enterprise value reported by a DCF remains pre-discount. When discounts\nare present, `enterprise_value - net_debt` reconciles to pre-discount\nequity value, not to the discounted fair-market equity value.",
      "properties": {
        "dloc": {
          "description": "Discount for Lack of Control (0.0–1.0, e.g., 0.20 for 20%).",
          "format": "double",
          "type": [
            "number",
            "null"
          ]
        },
        "dlom": {
          "description": "Discount for Lack of Marketability (0.0–1.0, e.g., 0.25 for 25%).",
          "format": "double",
          "type": [
            "number",
            "null"
          ]
        },
        "other_discount": {
          "description": "Additional discount (0.0–1.0).",
          "format": "double",
          "type": [
            "number",
            "null"
          ]
        }
      },
      "type": "object"
    }
  },
  "$id": "https://finstack_quant.dev/schemas/instrument/1/equity/discounted_cash_flow.schema.json",
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "description": "Discounted Cash Flow instrument for corporate equity valuation",
  "examples": [
    {
      "instrument": {
        "spec": {
          "attributes": {},
          "currency": "USD",
          "discount_curve_id": "USD-OIS",
          "flows": [
            [
              "2026-01-01",
              5000000.0
            ],
            [
              "2027-01-01",
              5750000.0
            ],
            [
              "2028-01-01",
              6500000.0
            ],
            [
              "2029-01-01",
              7250000.0
            ],
            [
              "2030-01-01",
              8000000.0
            ]
          ],
          "id": "DCF-TECH-CO",
          "mid_year_convention": true,
          "net_debt": 15000000.0,
          "pricing_overrides": {
            "adaptive_bumps": false,
            "call_friction_cents": null,
            "cds_quote_bp": null,
            "credit_spread_bump_bp": null,
            "implied_volatility": null,
            "mc_seed_scenario": null,
            "mean_reversion": null,
            "quoted_clean_price": null,
            "rate_bump_bp": null,
            "rho_bump_decimal": null,
            "spot_bump_pct": null,
            "theta_period": null,
            "tree_steps": null,
            "upfront_payment": null,
            "use_gobet_miri": false,
            "vega_bump_decimal": null,
            "vol_bump_pct": null,
            "vol_surface_extrapolation": "error",
            "ytm_bump_decimal": null
          },
          "shares_outstanding": 10000000.0,
          "terminal_value": {
            "growth_rate": 0.02,
            "type": "gordon_growth"
          },
          "valuation_date": "2025-01-01",
          "wacc": 0.1
        },
        "type": "discounted_cash_flow"
      },
      "schema": "finstack_quant.instrument/1"
    }
  ],
  "properties": {
    "instrument": {
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "description": "The Discounted Cash Flow instrument definition",
      "properties": {
        "spec": {
          "additionalProperties": false,
          "properties": {
            "attributes": {
              "$ref": "https://finstack_quant.dev/schemas/common/1/attributes.schema.json",
              "description": "Attributes for scenario selection and tagging"
            },
            "currency": {
              "$ref": "https://finstack_quant.dev/schemas/common/1/currency.schema.json",
              "description": "Currency for all cashflows."
            },
            "dilution_securities": {
              "description": "Dilutive securities (options, warrants, RSUs, convertibles) for treasury stock method.",
              "items": {
                "$ref": "#/$defs/DilutionSecurity"
              },
              "type": "array"
            },
            "discount_curve_id": {
              "$ref": "https://finstack_quant.dev/schemas/common/1/id.schema.json",
              "description": "Discount curve identifier, used for risk attribution only.\n\nDiscounting always uses [`wacc`](Self::wacc) via `(1 + wacc)^{-t}`\nregardless of whether this curve is loaded (the\nprevious behavior silently switched risky flows to risk-free curve\ndiscounting). Rate sensitivity (`Dv01`/`BucketedDv01`) bumps the\nrisk-free component inside the WACC instead."
            },
            "equity_bridge": {
              "anyOf": [
                {
                  "$ref": "#/$defs/EquityBridge"
                },
                {
                  "type": "null"
                }
              ],
              "description": "Structured equity bridge for EV-to-equity conversion.\n\nWhen present, takes precedence over the flat `net_debt` field."
            },
            "flows": {
              "description": "Explicit period free cash flows (date, amount pairs).",
              "items": {
                "maxItems": 2,
                "minItems": 2,
                "prefixItems": [
                  {
                    "type": "string"
                  },
                  {
                    "format": "double",
                    "type": "number"
                  }
                ],
                "type": "array"
              },
              "type": "array"
            },
            "id": {
              "$ref": "https://finstack_quant.dev/schemas/common/1/id.schema.json",
              "description": "Unique identifier for the DCF."
            },
            "mid_year_convention": {
              "default": false,
              "description": "Mid-year discounting convention (default: `false` = end-of-period).\n\nWhen `true`, each flow is discounted at `t` minus half the average\nflow spacing instead of `t` (the classic `t - 0.5` for annual\ngrids; half a period for sub-annual grids), reflecting the\nassumption that cash flows arrive mid-period. This is the standard\nconvention in IB/PE practice (Koller et al.). Exit-multiple\nterminal values are not shifted (point-in-time sale at the horizon).",
              "type": "boolean"
            },
            "net_debt": {
              "description": "Net debt (debt - cash) to subtract from enterprise value.\n\nIgnored when [`equity_bridge`](Self::equity_bridge) is `Some`.",
              "format": "double",
              "type": "number"
            },
            "pricing_overrides": {
              "$ref": "https://finstack_quant.dev/schemas/common/1/pricing_overrides.schema.json",
              "default": {
                "adaptive_bumps": false,
                "call_friction_cents": null,
                "cds_act360_include_last_day": false,
                "cds_aod_half_day_bias": false,
                "credit_spread_bump_bp": null,
                "mc_seed_scenario": null,
                "mean_reversion": null,
                "oas_price_basis": "settlement_dirty",
                "oas_quote_compounding": "continuous",
                "rate_bump_bp": null,
                "rho_bump_decimal": null,
                "spot_bump_pct": null,
                "theta_period": null,
                "tree_steps": null,
                "use_gobet_miri": false,
                "vega_bump_decimal": null,
                "vol_bump_pct": null,
                "vol_surface_extrapolation": "error",
                "ytm_bump_decimal": null
              },
              "description": "Attributes for tagging and scenarios."
            },
            "shares_outstanding": {
              "description": "Basic shares outstanding for per-share value calculation.",
              "format": "double",
              "type": [
                "number",
                "null"
              ]
            },
            "terminal_flow_override": {
              "description": "Annualized terminal flow used by growth-perpetuity terminal values.\n\nGordon Growth and H-Model capitalize an *annual* flow with annual\nWACC and growth rates. When the explicit `flows` grid is sub-annual\n(e.g. quarterly), the last flow is a period flow, not an annual one;\nset this to the trailing-twelve-month aggregate of the final\nexplicit year so the terminal value is computed on a consistent\nannual basis (Koller et al., Damodaran). When `None`, the last\nexplicit flow is used directly (correct for annual grids).\n\nIgnored by `ExitMultiple` terminal values.",
              "format": "double",
              "type": [
                "number",
                "null"
              ]
            },
            "terminal_value": {
              "$ref": "#/$defs/TerminalValueSpec",
              "description": "Terminal value specification."
            },
            "valuation_date": {
              "description": "Valuation date (as-of date for the DCF).",
              "format": "date",
              "type": "string"
            },
            "valuation_discounts": {
              "anyOf": [
                {
                  "$ref": "#/$defs/ValuationDiscounts"
                },
                {
                  "type": "null"
                }
              ],
              "description": "Private company valuation discounts (DLOM, DLOC)."
            },
            "wacc": {
              "description": "Weighted Average Cost of Capital (discount rate).",
              "format": "double",
              "type": "number"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "id",
            "currency",
            "flows",
            "wacc",
            "terminal_value",
            "net_debt",
            "valuation_date",
            "discount_curve_id",
            "attributes"
          ],
          "type": "object"
        },
        "type": {
          "const": "discounted_cash_flow",
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "type",
        "spec"
      ],
      "type": "object"
    },
    "schema": {
      "const": "finstack_quant.instrument/1",
      "description": "Schema version identifier",
      "type": "string"
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "schema",
    "instrument"
  ],
  "title": "Discounted Cash Flow",
  "type": "object"
}
